---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SocialIcon from '../../components/SocialIcon.astro';
import { AUTHOR, SITE_NAME, SITE_URL } from '../../consts';
import { absUrl } from '../../utils/images';

const authorUrl = new URL(AUTHOR.url, SITE_URL).href;
const imageUrl = absUrl(AUTHOR.image);

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: AUTHOR.name,
  url: authorUrl,
  image: imageUrl,
  jobTitle: AUTHOR.jobTitle,
  description: `Editor of ${SITE_NAME}. Full-time traveler with on-the-ground experience in ${AUTHOR.countriesVisited} countries.`,
  worksFor: {
    '@type': 'NewsMediaOrganization',
    name: SITE_NAME,
    url: SITE_URL,
  },
  sameAs: AUTHOR.sameAs,
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`${AUTHOR.name}, Editor`}
  description={`${AUTHOR.name} is the editor of ${SITE_NAME}. Full-time traveler with on-the-ground experience across ${AUTHOR.countriesVisited} countries — what breaking travel news means when you have actually been there.`}
  ogImage={AUTHOR.image}
  ogImageWidth={500}
  ogImageHeight={500}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <article class="article author-page">
    <header class="author-header">
      <img
        class="author-photo"
        src={AUTHOR.image}
        alt={`${AUTHOR.name}`}
        width="160"
        height="160"
      />
      <div class="author-header__text">
        <h1>{AUTHOR.name}</h1>
        <p class="author-role">Editor, {SITE_NAME}</p>
        <ul class="author-social">
          {
            AUTHOR.social.map((item) => (
              <li>
                <a
                  class="social-link"
                  href={item.href}
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer me"
                  aria-label={item.label}
                  title={item.label}
                >
                  <SocialIcon network={item.id} />
                </a>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="article__body">
      <p>
        {AUTHOR.name} is the editor of {SITE_NAME}. He reads breaking travel news
        the way a traveler does: does this change a flight, a border, a hotel
        night, or a trip you already booked — and what should you check before
        you react?
      </p>
      <p>
        That lens comes from living it. Since 2018 he has traveled full-time,
        lived on six continents, and visited{' '}
        <strong>{AUTHOR.countriesVisited} countries</strong> so far. Hundreds of
        flights and long stays in places from Jordan and Turkey to Southeast
        Asia, Africa, and Latin America mean a lot of the “what this means on
        the ground” framing here is not theoretical.
      </p>
      <p>
        When a story hits a place he has been recently, he pulls from that
        experience — sirens and local advice in Jordan, empty hotels when
        tourism drops, what embassy alerts looked like next to local news — and
        still cross-checks against current primary sources. Past trips are
        context, not a promise that conditions are the same today.
      </p>
      <p>
        He also knows the logistics side of long-term travel: second residency,
        banking across countries, visas, and border reality when plans change
        fast. He trained as a structural engineer at Université Laval and spent
        over a decade in the Ordre des ingénieurs du Québec — the same
        evidence-first habit shows up in how he edits travel news.
      </p>
      <p>
        Kevin is also co-founder of{' '}
        <a href="https://flytrippers.com/">Flytrippers</a>, where the deeper
        rewards and deal work lives. On {SITE_NAME}, the job is simpler: clear
        reporting on what just happened, and a practical take for people who
        actually travel.
      </p>
      <p>
        Originally from Québec. Featured in Canadian media including CBC’s{' '}
        <em>Dragons’ Den</em> with Flytrippers co-founder Andrew D’Amours.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
